{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Earth Goat|kanji=己未|romaji=tsuchinoto hitsuji|onyomi=kibi|p=jǐwèi|w=chi-wei|mi=t͡ɕi³⁵ weɪ̯|y=gei2 mei6|j=gei2 mei6|ci=kei mei|mc=kɨj mei|oc-bs=kɯʔ mei}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Earth Goat also known as 己未''' (tsuchinotohitsuji, kidonohitsuji, kibi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 56th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bokugo|ja|戊午}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚申}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Goat|ja|未}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

==己未の年==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 59 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Kibi|ja|己未}}.
{| class="wikitable"
|+'''己未の年'''
|-
! {{ill|1st Millennium|ja|1千年紀}} !! {{ill|2nd Millennium|ja|2千年紀}} !! {{ill|3rd Millennium|ja|3千年紀}}
|-
