'''Yin Earth Goat also known as 己未''' (tsuchinotohitsuji, kidonohitsuji, kibi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 56th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bokugo|ja|戊午}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚申}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Goat|ja|未}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

