It is the 56th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Bokugo|ja|戊午}} and followed by {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚申}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Goat|ja|未}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

==Yin Earth Goat (己未)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 59 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Kibi|ja|己未}}.
